76561198006329309,Not Recommended,282210,14859198,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,Dwaldor,"I don't usually write reviews, but in this case I needed to make an exception.97 minutes.Yep, that's how long it took to start up the game, futz around with it a bit looking for settings, reading the options for your new commander and then win.I know - it's a bit slow, but in my defense, I did actually read the initial missions thinking there would be something deeper there.  There isn't.Get enough energy to build your ships up to battleships, take enemy home planet (which gives you instantly everything they own) and rinse / repeat for however many players there are.  No need to build wonders, cities, or anything else meaningful (though I did waste at least half of that 97 minutes doing just that thinking it would matter.)Makes you wonder as to the replay value, though I suppose if I'm truly bored I can try a variety of the missions just to try them out.Sorry, Sid.  For as much entertainment your games have provided me over the years - this one just plain stinks."
