76561197996573674,Not Recommended,282210,14917335,"Posted: 16 March, 2015",all,Alex10301,"I know civilisation and games related to civilisation start out simple and boring, but i think this takes it to a new level.The settings screen is just 3 volume changers and a fullscreen button...There is no advanced game settings like Beyond Earth or Civ 5 that you can use to change map settings, specific AI's, etc...The missions and turn-based space combat is good though and kept me interested for a bit.Overall i would recommend not buying until there has been some major updates to improve the whole game and make it more interesting, like Beyond Earth"
76561198034397003,Recommended,282210,15397885,"Posted: 16 April, 2015",all,switt1313,"Overall I would recommend this game, not without a couple of warnings though.The game is fun to play and I'm sure to play it many more times... but there is also the first problem. It is a very short game. Personally I prefer the long drawn out building style or grand strategy games. This game can often be brought to conclusion (win or lose) in less than two hours, which for my personal taste is about two or three hundred hours too short ;) You are limited to one fleet which also makes it a bit too easy (no need to choose where precious resources are used)The other problem that ties in with the above is that it then also tends to get quite redundant quite quickly (which does not mean it cannot still be fun! - I do have a lot of fun with it). There is a limited number of missions, which although randomized by the terrain do tend to be ""always the same"".  There is always a ""Pirate Homeworld"" and a ""Marauder Homeworld"". And since there tends to be very limited time you can't really get much into planing long detailed ""reasearch paths"", because the game will be over long before you reach your goal. Part of this can be alleviated by playing a domination game, but even then time will still be very limited.So in conclusion:Fun to play (thus the thumbs up).But way too short."
