,Not Recommended,282210,14860299,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,Haggard Sauce,"As others wisely said (sadly, after it was too late for me) Avoid this pitfall of a game. This has got to be by far the dumbest-downed Sid Meier's game in history. Let me just list some things this game lacks that are just inexcusable in this age of gaming, no matter the price:1. Any form of Diplomacy or for that matter, interaction with other factions and AI players.2. The tutorial is hilariously lacking, even as a Civ 5/BE player with well over 1000 hours I struggled to understand what all I had to do and how to control the game both in battle and out of battle.3. Customization of your units by picking Harmony, Supremacy, or Purity at the beginning of the game ends there4. Basic information in tool tips is non existent5. Graphic Settings. Yes, that's right, there are absolutely no graphic settings. No resolution, no v-sync, heck you can't even change the brightness of the game. The only setting is full screen or not.6. Auto-Saves. Yep, there is no autosaves in the game, and no options to turn it onLoading from an In-Progress game. Made a mistake and want to reload? Sorry, exit to main menu and reload.7. Balancing is non-existent. On hard mode, factions will declare war with you within 5 turns of the game starting and will have ships that do ten times the damage yours are capable of. They will also take all of the planets possible, leaving you no resources to upgrade after your first turn.8. Settings in general are missing entirely. No key bindings, no controls explanation, no sound adjustments beyond volume level, no game customization beyond Race, Bonus, and opponents.Honestly, Beyond Earth stripped away dozens of features and I thought that this game was thier answer, that this would plug the gaping holes in thier most recent 4x Game. Unfortunately, they stripped it down even further to it's barest of bones, literally leaving you with a game so very simple that you can play with one hand on your mouse as you beat your head with a hammer held by the other hand for buying this game.Do not buy this game unless it's in the $2-$4 range, I'm not kidding, it's that terrible."
