,Recommended,282210,15836869,"Posted: 15 May, 2015",all,Bort,"This game has such a bad rep, because people see the name Sid Meier and assume 'Alpha Centauri 2!!!' You're wrong. It's a sci fi spinoff from Civilization: Beyond Earth.The galactic conquest and expansion side of the game plays in a similar fashion to the Civ games, albeit a very simplified version of Civ. The tech tree consists of 8 or 9 different fields of research, which can be upgraded from 0 to 8. Planets you conquer can have cities added to them, as well as a number of structures built to improve planetary resource income. These structures again go up to level 8, although there does not seem to be a limit on how many cities you can have.Each planet also has the possibility of being able to build a Wonder. Unlike the Civ games, these Wonders do not increase income or resources, but instead have a direct impact on your fleet.The fleet is the main part of the game. As with everything else, upgrading it is simple. There are a number of different options depending on what you want your ship to be good at, and the upgrades go up to level 8. You can also have up to 8 ships in your fleet.Space missions and encounters are the main part of the game. To bring new planets into your Empire, you need to do missions for them. They may limit you to a single ship for the mission, or you can take your entire fleet. Missions range from escape, to protect a colony ship, to defend from pirates, or capture an escaping fugitive.These missions take place in a fairly large area of space. The planet in question forms the centre of the map, and the mission takes place around it.  They are fun, easy to learn, and mistakes are rarely fatal (not at the normal difficulty levels anyways).One last touch I did like was when I was going for a domination victory. I defeated one race, leaving only two left on the map. Both of our Empires were pretty big, having split the galaxy almost down the middle. The next turn, I got a message from the NPC controlling the enemy faction, saying ""There's just the two of us left. It's been nice having peace with you for all these years, but what do you say we now find out which of us has the best Empire?"" Very friendly-like declaration of war. It's not about the conflict. It's about the honour."
76561197973836482,Not Recommended,282210,14876498,"Posted: 13 March, 2015",all,Geefunker,"Well this is the 2nd review I have ever done on Steam and I got to say. I would have not bought this game if I had a 2nd chance. I hoped for more depth, while all I got was something that feels like a tablet game ported to PC. I felt there was more to the Civ game on the Xbox and Windows phone than this.... I would have been happier with a modded version of Beyond Earth that was like the Final Fronter mod from Civ 4.If you want a game that might be good on an Ipad or Tablet, this is your game. You might not like it for PC."
