76561198010134705,Recommended,282210,21070163,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,Selva,"As usual, Steam's rating system is woefully inadequate.Do I recommend this?  Yes.  Buuuut... get it on sale.  I got this on sale as part of a bundle and am quite happy with that.  Had I paid the original... what was it? $20 I think.... I would have been p(censored)ed.  But as it is I'm pleased.  For what, a few years ago, I would have spent for an evening at an arcade, I got a good solid evening entertainment out of it.  And I will probably play it again… one day when I’m bored but too lazy for a console game.Is this a great strategy game?  Eh… no.  Tech trees are linear, ship upgrades are entirely statistical and you get one and only one fleet.  you can add ships and upgrade them individually.  but you can only ever have the 1 fleet.  Planets can have bots defending them but they, as far as I can tell, they (the bots) can not be upgraded.  (Planets can.) And on the subject of planets, each planet gets it's own personal exclusive wonder that you can build.  1 per.  No options as to what.  Happy Birthday.That said, the battles are fun.  Which is good since this is pretty combat heavy,  The opposing AI is not stupid.  (Which is refreshing for a space game.)  Lots of asteroids and stuff to fly around.  AND for this first time in a space strategy game (outside of MOO3 which I believe I am one of 4 people on Earth that did not hate) fighters actually are worth a c(censored)p.So... Is it recommended?  Yes.  Is it worthy of the Sid Meier name?  Eeeehhhh... no.  More like high end Kongregate stuff.    (Though the voice acting is good.)Oh... sort of an after thought here.  The story... you know the bit about hearing a distant call for help and stuff...  Makes no sense what so ever.  It certainly doesn't seem to have ANYTHING to do with the game.  Who were these guys?  No idea.  Do you ever encounter them?  Not that I have seen.  Or maybe I did and it just wasn't mentioned.  Played through.  P