,Not Recommended,282210,14992377,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,JoeWhizer,"After playing an half of an hour, I can say that - at the current stage - it's not worth buying.A lot of serious issues on the PC version. There is already a guide available how to bypass/workaround the most issues, but some of this won't work for me. For example:1. Borderless FullscreenThe game offers a borderless fullscreen mode to play. When you activate it, you still have your Windows taskbar visible. You can workaround this issue by using the tool ""Borderless Gaming"". This really works good.2. Not able to save the gameIn some circumstances you won't be able to save the game: special character in steam user name, not running in admin mode, running the wrong executable (i.e. 32bit on 64bit). Most of this is not working for me. I really don't want to change my user name to be able to save in a game. That is weird. They should be able to fix this, other games (also Beyond Earth) works fine with saving. Also in Steam Cloud, so why?3. Game is crashing in the introThe workaround described in the link below is not working for me. I need to just bypass the intro by clicking left mouse. If you forget to click, game over.For me it seems the game had absolutely no testing at all. That would explain the price. My recommendation is currently to wait for a major patch that addresses the most issues. If you still decide to buy this game, then make yourself aware of the workarounds:http://segmentnext.com/2015/03/13/sid-meiers-starships-errors-bugs-crashes-full-screen-save-game-and-fixes/I will update this review once a patch is available and the game would maybe playable for me. Currently it's not because saving is not working for me."
