76561198111560731,Recommended,282210,14895729,"Posted: 14 March, 2015",all,TerranceFarrel,"This is not Civilization, Or Galactic Civilizato, Or Masters of Orion.You are an admiral. You lead your ships, run missions, earn influence of the worlds you visit.The emphasis is tactical. Expect to spend a lot of time on a battlemap.Lasers are long range but planets block them and asteroids can block them or reduce damage. (There are a LOT of asteroids on a map!)Plasma weapons do more damge but are shorter range.Torpedoes are area affect and can pass through asteroids. Great for flushing quarry from a spot thats too good.You also have fighters, stealth systems, shields...You will build wonders, improvements and the like, but as I said, the emphasis is tactical or these elements are lighter fare.The game can be small and played quickly. The hardest victory conditions on the biggest map is about a six hour affair on easy level.A lot of people complain about the small window but playing full screen is trivial. There is a fullscreen button you can click in the menues...you can also simply maximize the window.A lot of people want a longer game...I recommend if you feel that way you play a ""Population"" victory, or ""Domination"" if you want an even longer game.In the end there is not as much here as there is in Civ or Beyond Earth. Then again, look at the price tag...On a 1 to 10 I give it an 8.2It's entertaining."
