76561198065829183,Recommended,282210,14878427,"Posted: 14 March, 2015",all,SlimSlamKablam,"I think most of the negative reviews around this came come mostly as a result of overly high expectations. A lot of the criticism is that it's not as in depth as civ, or other great 4x titles for that matter. But the fact is, this game isn't trying to be complex. Let's not forget that ""Sid Meier's"" games are not confined to complex strategy games. I've had just as much in my time playing Sid Meier's Pirates as I have playing Civ, and the difficulty gap between those games is enourmous. Just because this game is light on strategy doesn't mean it should be a let down. Also, this game was barely mentioned at all until a few months before its release; clearly this game isn't supposed to be a big deal.What's more, it really shouldn't matter if it's a mobile game, because it's still a good game. The only reason mobile games are a bad thing is that they are frequenty riddled with poor design and are little more than money-making schemes for their developers. I think it's good that Starships is a mobile game. You know why? It sets a good example. More mobile games should be like this. It's relatively simple, has a low learning curve, and yet still manages to be engaging and entertaining.It's easy to enjoy this game as long as you don't go into it expecting to play a 12 hour long game. I finish games in 30 minutes to 1 hour, and that's fine, because for what it is, this game is great."
