76561198026937562,Recommended,282210,14882140,"Posted: 14 March, 2015",all,dantewashere,"This is NOT an epic strategy game with the level of detail of a Civ 1-5 or a MOO (if you want to think of space strategy games). If you don't have those expectations upfront, then the game can be interesting in it's own way. At it's most basic level, Starships is actually ""Ace Patrol"" set in space with themes from Beyond Earth thrown in. The battle hex board layout is exactly the same as Ace Patrol, but the mechanics of how weapons play out is now space themed. There is definiely more detail here than in Ace Patrol when you look at all aspects of the game. There is a simplified research system, planets that are ""upgradeable"" to harvest more resources for upgrading your ships. All of this is simplified to a point where each aspect of the game could be thought of as an upgrade system, less discovery, and faster. The mission system is also simple and can get a little repetitive, but by mid-game it becomes only battles against other empires. This is a mobile game for the most part, but I don't mind playing a quick game on the PC when I have a moment. Some might say it's not worth $15, but that's actually cheap compared to the $50 epic game. For a fast playing strategy game with more depth than an ""Ace Patrol"", Starships is definitely worth it. The expectations around this game were poorly set up, so watch a gameplay video to decide if it's right for you."
