,Recommended,282210,14861656,"Posted: 13 March, 2015",all,Teknomage01,"I am very thankful I paid no attention to any of the hype for this game.. why? Because I didn't have undue expecations, so I think this game is fun! Yes, its simple.. its meant to be. Thats a good thing to me (and I play a lot of very complex deep games). The menu is sparse? Well.. its meant to be simple, so why would a simple game have a complex menu? You can easily playthrough a whole game in one night.. and again, thats not a bad thing! Its a quick and simple setup ""boardgame"" style and thats what makes it great! What more could you want for just $15?I have played every. single. sid meier. game. ever. And this game is not bad. Is it alpha centauri in space? No. Its not meant to be. No its not perfect, no game is anymore, not at launch anyway (devs need real feedback from players first, they can't read out minds). I think this game has a lot of potential down the road, especially with integration into civ: beyond earth.A few things I would like to see is a bit more information for the missions before I send my fleet there... some of those missions are brutal! Also, more than one fleet would be especially nice. The game is playable with only one fleet of ships though.Bottom line: if you want a fun, simple, quick and easy(ish) game for cheap that ties into civ: be that can be played in an evening than this is good game for that. If you enjoy tactical turn-based battles and some micromanagment thats not overly complicated this game is good for you. I could easily see this as an actual boardgame someday too, complete with starship figures!"
