76561197999005229,Recommended,282210,14862132,"Posted: 13 March, 2015",all,Sevin Church,"Despite what others have said this game is great. Why they link it to Pirates is unknown to me, it is more like Civ meets Air Patrol. The civ part requires very little management and the fleet system is so much fun to customize. By customize I don't mean the look of the ships, rather how tough, fast, how many hangars, etc. And if you want to reduce points you spent from say stealth to engine, you can in no time flat.It does lack fullscreen mode at this point. But I've played worse games in fullscreen and some awesome games in windowed mode. I'd like to see it added, but I am not gonna whine and say it ruins the whole game. That's extremely petty when the game has much to offer to keep you busy.I think some folks are getting a bad impression of this game because of the lack of micro-management. To me that gets you in to the action that much faster, which is the point of this game. I've already spent hours conquering the galaxy. The maps aren't very huge, in this type of game they don't need to be. You don't have to exhaust yourself building 40 structures from the ground up like you do in Civ, that's a major plus for me. Although I love Civ, I didn't need another one so soon.For the current cost of the game, it is great. It can use some polish, what game can't use some 5 years after it's launched?Update: I expected to get some down votes, can't expect children to understand simple logic with out getting their panties in a bunch I guess. Bottom line, the game is worth the money, don't expect to be wow'ed. It's a simple game, lots of fun."
