76561198025840779,Recommended,282210,14859912,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,MandatoryHashTags,"I spent a few hours playing this today. I have not played Beyond Earth. I've enjoyed the game so far.What it is:A $15.00 space title, with tactical combat, decent graphics, and some compelling aspects.Ship customization (modular)Tech TreeLightweight turn based systemLow maintenance.This is a great game to play on your ipad or machine when you have a couple of hours to burn and want to unwind after work. It is not a Civ game and will not have that level of cmplexity. I think it has potential to be very moddable if they make that an option.Now with that said there are some things people need to know:The tech tree is very imited and has no appreciable effect outside of combatThe game centers around space combat and gathering territoryYou can only have 8 ships and they always travel as a groupIt can feel a little rinse and repeat in the late game on Epic stick to shorter gamesNone of those things surprise me this is not a $50.00 game. What it does not have is any bugs I have found, it performs perfectly, and I have had fun playing it. I like space games, I like to unwind, I do not like to feel like I am managing an empire when I get off work during the week. This is exactly what I expected when I bought it, I watched a lot of game play videos from the creators before buying.I suggest if you like science fiction and want something to play thats simple and fun. Give it a try, watch a few videos first if you are unsure.If however, you are expecting the next Orions, Civ in Space, Galactic Civ or what have you then you will be dissapointed. It plays like a lightweight X-Com in space. This would not be a game for you.Hope this helps!"
